UID:10024049-1774029600-1778536800@evanstonmade.org
SUMMARY:Glow Wild: A Lantern Festival of Hope
DESCRIPTION:From March 19 through May 10\, experience Glow Wild: A Lantern Festival of Hope — a breathtaking journey of light\, art\, and conservation. Wander paths under the moonlight\, illuminated by handcrafted lanterns representing wildlife and mythology from around the world. \nLaunching on the cusp of the spring equinox\, each evening will shine with culture and community. Enjoy live performances\, global music and dance\, storytelling\, and unique food experiences. Your ticket also includes rides on the Carousel and the Ferris Wheel\, plus event parking. Select nights — March 26\, April 16\, and May 7 — feature sensory-friendly programming\, allowing guests of all ages and abilities to share in the magic. \nJoin us Thursdays through Sundays March 19-May 10 for Glow Wild: A Lantern Festival of Hope — a culturally unique celebration of beauty\, hope\, and the enduring connection between all living things. During these special evenings\, all animal habitats will be closed to ensure the comfort and well-being of our animals. We can’t wait to welcome you for a vibrant celebration of lights\, global cuisine\, and cultural traditions. Your support truly helps advance animal care and conservation. \nMar 19\, 2026\, 6:00pm to\nMay 10\, 2026\, 10:00pm Timezone: Central Time (US & Canada)
URL:https://evanstonmade.org/event/glow-wild-a-lantern-festival-of-hope/2026-03-20/
LOCATION:Brookfield Zoo Chicago\, 31st Street and Golfview Avenue\, Brookfield\, IL\, 60513\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://evanstonmade.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Glow-Wild.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Brookfield Zoo Chicago":MAILTO:info@brookfieldzoo.org
END:VEVENT
